items.title: Americans Are Actually More United Than You Might Think
items.description: Americans think of our society as so divided. Might there be some upside to starting the new year knowing we aren’t as polarized as we thought?

items.title: Angelina Jolie and Brad Pitt Settle Divorce After Eight Years
items.description: The settlement resolves a key part of the protracted end of their very public Hollywood romance.

items.title: Germany’s Chancellor Scholz Takes a Jab at Musk in New Year’s Eve Address
items.description: Chancellor Olaf Scholz said Germany’s election would “not be decided by the owners of social media channels” in his annual New Year’s Eve address.

items.title: Puerto Rico Power Outages Plunge Many Into Darkness on New Year’s Eve

items.title: Victim of Coney Island Subway Immolation Is Identified by the Police
items.description: Debrina Kawam of Toms River, N.J., was burned alive on Dec. 22 in a videotaped killing that shocked New York.
